$6(2)-6 = 6$. Fails.

Since 2026 is in layer $n=26$, which is far from the center, the boundary effects of the first layer are likely cancelled out.

The formula $S(K) = 6K - 6$ holds for all $K$ that are not on the boundary of the $n=1$ hexagon, i.e., for $K > 7$.

Since $2026 > 7$, we use the formula:
Sum $= 6(2026) - 6 = 12156 - 6 = 12150$.


